Etymology 1[edit]

ad- +‎ premō

Alternative forms[edit]

  • adprimō

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈap.pri.moː/, [ˈap.pɾɪ.moː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈap.pri.mo/, [ˈap.pri.mɔ]

Verb[edit]

apprimō (present infinitive apprimere, perfect active appressī, supine appressum); third conjugation

  1. I press close to

Etymology 2[edit]

Regularly declined forms of apprīmus.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /apˈpriː.moː/, [apˈpɾiː.moː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /apˈpri.mo/, [apˈpriː.mɔ]

Adjective[edit]

apprīmō

  1. dative masculine singular of apprīmus
  2. dative neuter singular of apprīmus
  3. ablative masculine singular of apprīmus
  4. ablative neuter singular of apprīmus
